  "texts": [
    "After 30 min on ice, cells were divided into 250-μL aliquots and flash-frozen in liquid nitrogen.",
    "Competent cells were stored at -80 °C until use.",
    "The pReg-RamR and Pramr-GFP plasmids were co-transformed into DH10B cells, which were then plated on LB agar plates containing appropriate antibiotics.",
    "Three separate colonies were picked for each transformation and were grown overnight.",
    "The following day, 20 μL of each culture was then used to inoculate six separate wells in a 2-mL 96deep-well plate (Corning, P-DW-20-C-S) sealed with an AeraSeal film (Excel Scientific) containing 900 μL LB medium, one for each test ligand and a solvent control."
